news.title: China considers plan to help Vanke repay $6.8 billion debt
news.para: The proposal involves regulators allocating 20 billion yuan in special local government bonds to buy unsold properties and vacant land from Vanke, the report on Wednesday said, citing people familiar with the matter.

news.title: Shriram Properties' net profit dips 29.82% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Shriram Properties' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 179.87 crore in Q3 FY25, a dip of 25.23 per cent from Rs 240.57 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Nashik civic body revives industrial property tax slab
news.para: The civic administration has started implementing the order of the former NMC chief Ashok Karanjkar issued on Sept 20 last year.

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit grows 11.86% in Q3 FY25
news.para: Kamdhenu's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 172.65 crore in Q3 FY25, a growth of 9.66 per cent from Rs 157.44 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Maharashtra to register builders & contractors under board of construction workers
news.para: The move comes a week after the state launched online registration system for the workers, which has already received over 5 lakh applications.

news.title: Tamil Nadu's registration department collects Rs 237.9 crore on February 11
news.para: Accepting the public's request and to accommodate high demand, the govt increased advance booking slots. Offices with one sub-registrar had 150 slots instead of 100, while those with two sub-registrars had 300 instead of 200.

news.title: Over 2,100 illegal structures demolished in four days in Pune's Kudalwadi
news.para: These establishments operated without consent from PCMC's building permission department and Maharashtra Pollution Control Board. Besides, the labour laws were also not followed by the owners.

news.title: Will construct 30 lakh more houses under PMAY-Rural: Uttar Pradesh deputy CM
news.para: The Centre plans to construct another two crore houses in the next phase of the scheme which is set to be accelerated in the 2025-26 fiscal.

news.title: Kamarhati civic body issues 'express order' to raze 57 illegal buildings
news.para: The order follows the detection of several tilted buildings in Belgharia, Baranagar, and Kamarhati.

news.title: Building debris choking Ahmedabad's lakes
news.para: ​The AMC set up 25 sites in the city for dumping demolition and renovation waste. However, sources said that when citizens call up the AMC staff to have demolition waste picked up, it is not done promptly and a fee of Rs 200 is charged per trip.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body to use drones to map Madhuban Bapudham township
news.para: The survey data will be superimposed on the zonal map of the township. The survey was necessary to keep track of its land records by employing the latest technology, officials said.

news.title: Arkade Developers to redevelop 6.5 acres in Dahisar East, Mumbai
news.para: The redevelopment project, which spans a plot area of 26,286 sq meters, is projected to generate a grossdevelopment value (GDV) of Rs 1,700 crore approximately.

news.title: Gauhar Khan buys three apartments for Rs 10.13 crore in Versova, Mumbai
news.para: While one transaction was registered solely in Khan’s name, the other two apartments were purchased along with her husband, Zaid Darbar. All transactions were registered in February 2025.

news.title: Raised property tax recovery target too steep for Ludhiana civic body
news.para: With the financial year nearing its end, officials now consider strict enforcement measures, including a sealing campaign, to bridge the gap.

news.title: Greater Cochin development body seeks metropolitan authority status
news.para: The proposal aims to strengthen the organisation's role in urban development rather than dissolving it. Recently, GCDA raised the demand at the meeting of the seventh State Finance Commission.

news.title: 91Springboard adds one lakh sq ft across three centers in NCR
news.para: The three new hubs are World Trade Center, Nauroji Nagar, New Delhi, DLF 14B, Cyber City, Gurugram and Bhutani Avenue 62, Noida

news.title: NCLAT asks Supertech to pay December salaries to around 300 employees
news.para: The 300-odd workers, who have been without pay since Sept last year, recently approached the NCLAT, seeking its intervention and an order to IRP to clear the dues.

news.title: Haryana RERA seizes security deposits of six developers for violating registry rules
news.para: In a major crackdown on errant developers, the authority in the city also imposed penalties of Rs 25 lakh each on two promoters for not adhering to project timelines, as mandated under Section 4(2)(l)(C) of the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016.

news.title: Telangana RERA penalises builder for delay, orders it to pay interest to buyer till handover of flat
news.para: The complainant, who purchased a flat in Block-II of ‘Parijatha Pride', had alleged that despite paying Rs 27.50 lakh between Oct 2020 and Nov 2021, Parijatha Homes & Developers Pvt. Ltd. failed to hand over possession of the flat within the agreed time.

news.title: Pay interest to homebuyers for handover delay: Haryana RERA to Orris Infrastructure
news.para: The dispute centred around a 2BHK apartment in Tower 2A of Aster Court in Sector 85 where the complainants claimed the developer altered project plans and imposed unjustified additional charges.
